LINE.Text: A trauma to the head could in some instances lead to a brain injury If a child has sustained a brain injury they may
show a variety of symptoms If is likely that the symptoms displayed will differ depending on the severity of the brain injury.
It a child sustains a trauma to the head which leads to a bruise or a bump but remains conscious medical attention is not always necessary
However parents should remain vigilant for the signs of a more serious injury for at least 24 hours following a trauma to the head
If a child begins to display any of the symptoms listed below, or if a child loses consciousness
then parents should sock urgent medical attention
Let's take a look at the different symptoms of a brain injury in children.
Medical attention should be sought immediately
if any of the following symptoms are apparent in
a child after a head impact:
Loss of vision, blurred vision or
